elements.title: Soiscél Molaisse
elements.contents: ... that the medieval Irish book shrine known as the Soiscél Molaisse (pictured) was built in three phases, from the 8th to the 14th or 15th centuries?

elements.title: Carroll Best
elements.contents: ... that bluegrass musician Carroll Best is credited for developing a melodic three-finger banjo style that influenced Tony Trischka and Béla Fleck?

elements.title: Black Boots
elements.contents: ... that the British South Africa Police's Black Boots support unit were dubbed "terr hungry" for apparently enjoying killing suspected terrorists in Rhodesia?

elements.title: Eshmunazar I
elements.contents: ... that Eshmunazar I, the Phoenician king of Sidon, participated in the Neo-Babylonian campaigns against Egypt, where he seized stone sarcophagi belonging to members of the Egyptian elite?

elements.title: Regine Velasquez
elements.contents: ... that Regine Velasquez, a Filipino singer and actress, was the first Asian artist to stage a solo concert at the Carnegie Hall in New York City?

elements.title: Tetris Holding won an injunction
elements.contents: ... that Tetris Holding won an injunction in 2012 to stop sales of a video game clone of their famed Tetris game?

elements.title: Roy Beddington
elements.contents: ... that artist Roy Beddington illustrated three books with Irish author Stephen Gwynn and competed in the painting event at the 1948 Summer Olympics?

elements.title: Citicorp Center
elements.contents: ... that an inquiry from an engineering student led to the repair of a structural flaw at New York City's Citicorp Center?
